Judul: Dark-matter hunt comes up empty: Results prompt physicists to rethink their theories
Abstrak:
Physicists are growing ever more frustrated in their hunt for dark matter — the massive but hard-to-detect substance that is thought to comprise 85% of the material Universe. Teams working with the world’s
most sensitive dark-matter detectors report that they have failed to find the particles, and that the ongoing drought has challenged theorists’ prevailing views
Fakultas: Fakultas Matematika dan Ilmu Pengetahuan Alam
